# Code Style and Structure

## Project Structure

```
src/
  app/             # Expo Router pages (file-based routing only)
  assets/          # Static files: images/, svg/, videos/, fonts/
  components/
    ui/            # Reusable themed UI primitives (Button, Card, etc.)
    icons/         # Icon components
    wallet/        # Wallet-specific components
    general/       # Header, ScreenWrapper, WalletIdenticon, UserIcon, etc.
    profile/       # LogDisplay, ContactUs, DeveloperPanel
    app-providers.tsx  # Root provider wrapper
    app-theme.tsx      # Theme provider
    error-boundary.tsx # Error boundary
    auth-guard.tsx    # Auth redirect logic
  constants/       # App config, theme colors, Solana constants
  hooks/           # Custom React hooks + Zustand stores
  types/           # TypeScript type definitions
  utils/           # Helper/utility functions
  lib/
    api/           # API layer (Orval, Axios, token store)
    network/       # Network status (e.g. useNetworkStatus)
    utils.ts       # Shared utils (e.g. cn)
```

## Rules

- Only route files belong in `src/app/` — all other code goes in components, hooks, utils, etc.
- One component per file. File name matches the exported component.
- Barrel exports (`index.ts`) in each folder for clean imports.
- Use `@/` path alias for all imports from `src/` (e.g., `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/Button'`).
- Keep files under 200 lines. Extract logic into hooks/utils if a file grows large.
- Colocate related code: wallet components near wallet hooks, etc.
